COMMENT	Ih-current	Made threadsafe (CCohen)	Removed dt as a PARAMETER, to ensure variable time step integration (CCohen)	Removed: INDEPENDENT {t FROM 0 TO 1 WITH 1 (ms)}, to allow t > 1ms. t remains	independent by default (CCohen)	Added scaling factor to STATE (CCohen)ENDCOMMENTUNITS {		(mA) = (milliamp)	(mV) = (millivolt)    (mM) = (milli/liter)}PARAMETER {	v 				(mV)    eh = -47  		(mV) 		: ih-reversal potential by Berger	  	gbar = 0.00015	(mho/cm2)	: density on dendrite assuming 150pA current and 150mV driving force (=200pS/um2)	}NEURON {		SUFFIX ih	NONSPECIFIC_CURRENT Ih	RANGE Ih, gbar	THREADSAFE}STATE {		h 	<1e-2>}ASSIGNED {		Ih	(mA/cm2)}INITIAL {		h = alpha(v)/(beta(v)+alpha(v))}BREAKPOINT {		SOLVE state METHOD cnexp	Ih = gbar*h*(v-eh)}DERIVATIVE state {     	: exact when v held constant; integrates over dt step	h' = (1-h) * alpha(v) - h * beta(v)}FUNCTION alpha(v) {		: parameters are estimated by direct fitting of HH model to activation time constants and voltage actication curve recorded at 34C by M. Kole	alpha = 0.001 * 6.43 * (v + 154.9)/(exp((v + 154.9)/11.9) - 1)	}FUNCTION beta(v) {		beta = 0.001 * 193 * exp(v/33.1)}